Interesting video explaining what food insecurity precisely means?
https://hungerandhealth.feedingamerica.org/understand-food-insecurity/hunger-health-101/


The idea behind is that food insecurity is not just hunger : it is not leading a "healthy and active life" because the food consumed can be low quality or not in a sufficient quantity. 
This provokes obesity or hunger. Moreover food insecurity if a big box with many subsets. Food insecurity is caracterised by having to made trade-offs because not enough money for everything (electricity, water, etc.)



